spinupDelay.name: spinupDelay
spinupDelay.description: This is the Spinup Delay for Spinning Up Physical Drives at Firmware Initialization Time. The Physical Drives are divided into Groups, each containing the number of drives indicated by the spinupCount variable. spinupDelay variable is the amount of delay used before the drives in the next group are issued a SPINUP Command.

spinupCount.name: spinupCount
spinupCount.description: This is the Spinup Count for Spinning up Physical Drives at Firmware Initialization Time. The Physical Drives are divided into Groups, each containing the number of drives indicated by this variable. All the drives in a group are issued SPINUP Command without any delay. Next group is given SPINUP Commands after a delay indicated by the spinupDelay variable.
